K-Masstec: “Knowledge-driven design of management strategies
for stem canker specific resistance genes”, INRA Metaprogramme SMaCH,
PRESUME action, 2013–2016. The project aims at developing efficient strategies for the deployment of genetic resistance in the field, based on knowledge issued from the understanding of the molecular interaction between distinct avirulence genes, and mainly the discovery of non-conventional gene-for-gene interactions.
